    {"id": "DOC-001", "title": "Solar Panel Maintenance SOP v4", "category": "sop", "status": "published", "content": "## Standard Operating Procedure\n\n### Solar Panel Maintenance\n\n**Scope:** All photovoltaic installations under ADIP management.\n\n**Frequency:** Quarterly inspection with annual deep maintenance.\n\n**Procedure:**\n1. Visual inspection of all panels for cracks, delamination, or discoloration\n2. Thermal imaging scan to identify hot spots\n3. Electrical performance verification (I-V curve tracing)\n4. Cleaning schedule based on soiling index\n5. Connection torque verification\n6. Inverter performance check\n\n**Safety:** LOTO procedures must be followed. All work at height requires harness inspection within last 6 months.", "summary": "Standard operating procedure for quarterly solar panel maintenance including inspection, cleaning, and performance verification.", "author": "Technical Standards Team", "version": 4, "createdAt": "2026-01-15T10:00:00Z", "updatedAt": "2026-06-01T14:30:00Z", "tags": ["solar", "maintenance", "sop", "safety"], "fileSize": 245000, "pageCount": 12, "language": "en", "sourceUrl": "/knowledge/DOC-001", "relatedAssets": ["SP-101", "SP-102", "SP-103"], "relatedEvidence": ["EV-001", "EV-002"], "relatedRecommendations": ["R-001"]},
