    {"id": "DOC-003", "title": "Transformer Oil Analysis Best Practices", "category": "best_practice", "status": "published", "content": "# Transformer Oil Analysis Best Practices\n\n## Key Parameters\n\n### Dissolved Gas Analysis (DGA)\n- Hydrogen (H\u2082): >100 ppm indicates partial discharge\n- Methane (CH\u2084): >50 ppm indicates arcing\n- Ethylene (C\u2082H\u2084): >100 ppm indicates thermal fault\n- Acetylene (C\u2082H\u2082): >10 ppm indicates severe arcing\n\n### Oil Quality\n- Dielectric strength: >30 kV (new), >20 kV (in service)\n- Moisture content: <20 ppm (new), <35 ppm (in service)\n- Acidity: <0.1 mg KOH/g (in service)\n- Interfacial tension: >25 mN/m\n\n### Sampling Frequency\n- Critical transformers (>100 MVA): quarterly\n- Standard transformers: semi-annual\n- Distribution transformers: annual\n\n### Interpretation\n- Use Duval Triangle method for fault type identification\n- Consider loading history when evaluating results\n- Trending is more valuable than single measurements", "summary": "Best practices for transformer oil analysis including DGA interpretation, oil quality thresholds, and sampling frequency guidelines.", "author": "Laboratory Services", "version": 2, "createdAt": "2025-08-10T12:00:00Z", "updatedAt": "2026-03-20T16:00:00Z", "tags": ["transformer", "oil-analysis", "best-practice", "dga"], "fileSize": 320000, "pageCount": 15, "language": "en", "sourceUrl": "/knowledge/DOC-003", "relatedAssets": ["TF-101", "TF-102", "TF-201"], "relatedEvidence": ["EV-004"], "relatedRecommendations": ["R-003"]},
