    {"id": "DOC-005", "title": "Emergency Response Playbook - Grid Failure", "category": "playbook", "status": "published", "content": "# Emergency Response Playbook: Grid Failure\n\n## Activation Criteria\n- Complete loss of grid connection >5 minutes\n- Partial grid failure affecting >25% of capacity\n- Black start required\n\n## Immediate Actions (First 15 Minutes)\n1. **Isolate failed section** - Open all breakers on affected bus\n2. **Assess situation** - Determine scope and cause\n3. **Notify stakeholders** - Grid operator, key customers, regulatory body\n4. **Activate backup systems** - Battery storage, backup generators\n\n## Recovery Phase\n1. **Black start procedure** - Restart primary generation sources\n2. **Synchronize** - Match phase and frequency\n3. **Reconnect loads** - Prioritize critical infrastructure\n4. **Stabilize** - Monitor frequency and voltage\n\n## Post-Event\n- Incident report within 24 hours\n- Root cause analysis within 7 days\n- Update playbook based on lessons learned", "summary": "Emergency response playbook for grid failure scenarios including immediate actions, recovery procedures, and post-event requirements.", "author": "Emergency Response Team", "version": 5, "createdAt": "2025-06-15T10:00:00Z", "updatedAt": "2026-04-10T11:00:00Z", "tags": ["emergency", "grid-failure", "playbook", "black-start"], "fileSize": 520000, "pageCount": 25, "language": "en", "sourceUrl": "/knowledge/DOC-005", "relatedAssets": ["TF-101", "TF-201", "BB-101"], "relatedEvidence": ["EV-007"], "relatedRecommendations": ["R-004", "R-005"]},
    {"id": "DOC-006", "title": "Battery Storage Safety Guidelines", "category": "policy", "status": "published", "content": "# Battery Storage Safety Guidelines\n\n## General Safety\n- All personnel must complete battery safety training annually\n- PPE: insulated gloves, face shield, flame-resistant clothing\n- No metal jewelry or loose conductive items\n- Two-person rule for all high-voltage work\n\n## Fire Safety\n- Class D fire extinguishers at all battery locations\n- Automatic gas detection and ventilation\n- Thermal runaway detection system\n- Emergency ventilation activation at 60\u00b0C\n\n## Operational Limits\n- Do not exceed 90% SOC for extended periods\n- Minimum SOC: 10% for Li-ion, 20% for flow batteries\n- Operating temperature: 15-35\u00b0C\n- Maximum charge/discharge rate: 1C continuous\n\n## Maintenance\n- Weekly: visual inspection, temperature check\n- Monthly: connection torque check, capacity test\n- Quarterly: BMS firmware update check, calibration", "summary": "Comprehensive safety guidelines for battery storage systems covering operational limits, fire safety, and maintenance procedures.", "author": "Safety Committee", "version": 2, "createdAt": "2025-09-01T09:00:00Z", "updatedAt": "2026-05-01T10:00:00Z", "tags": ["battery", "safety", "guidelines", "training"], "fileSize": 280000, "pageCount": 14, "language": "en", "sourceUrl": "/knowledge/DOC-006", "relatedAssets": ["BB-101", "BB-102", "BB-103"], "relatedEvidence": ["EV-008", "EV-009"], "relatedRecommendations": ["R-006"]},
